A half of the partnership tokens are designated for associate companies and advisors, while the other half is allocated for the community impulse program. The code for the ALS Token allocation is open sourced and can be accessed on GitHub.   Impulse Campaign Token Allocation:  Participants will get impulses during the campaign. At the end of the campaign each participant will get an amount of ALS tokens proportional to the amount of impulses they acquired. If all the ALS tokens will be sold during the ICO, the Community Impulse Campaign fund will represent ~5,000,000 ALS, that will be distributed among participants. Official CryptoAlias BB Signature -> HERE  Rules To be eligible for the weekly reward, a participant must have the CryptoAlias signature 24 hours a day for 7 days in a row. Users with negative trust are not eligible for the Community Impulse Campaign. Users found spamming will be immediately and permanently disqualified, reported to the moderators, and banned from any other campaign.
